    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips </strong>to a <strong>baking paper-</strong>lined baking tray (or two!) with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>dried cranberries</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>in a large bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong>, the <strong>chopped cranberries </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>cranberry slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash then <strong>remove leaves</strong> (2 per person!) from your <strong>lettuce</strong> and set aside, roughly shred the <strong>inner core</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>southern fried seasoning</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>to a large bowl with 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and mix until completely combined</p><p>Add your <strong>turkey steaks</strong> to the bowl with 25ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[35ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[50ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and, using your hands, scrunch the flour onto the turkey until fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated turkey</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat (enough to cover the whole base of the pan)</p><p>Once hot, reduce the heat to medium-high, add the <strong>coated turkey </strong>to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden, crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once done, season the <strong>cooked turkey</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>southern fried turkey</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your<strong> brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Once everything is almost ready, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut side up</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-turkey-burger-and-brussels-sprout-buffalo-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build the burger, top the <strong>warmed brioche base </strong>with the <strong>outer lettuce leaves</strong>, some of the <strong>cranberry slaw</strong>, the <strong>southern fried turkey</strong>,<strong> </strong>a<strong> </strong>generous dollop of your <strong>Brussels sprout buffalo sauce </strong>and a <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>brioche</strong> <strong>lid</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>southern fried turkey burger</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>shredded gem </strong>with the <strong>remaining cranberry slaw</strong> and serve it to the side with the <strong>chips</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
